Hello, All.

I'm user of Samsung SyncMaster 971p. It presence in support base. And I want 
to use MagicRotate function (portrait mode) of my monitor.

I use nvidia driver (180.22).

It is easy to rotate picture on the screen with xrandr. But I don't know how 
to get event when display is in portrait mode. 

I can see current mode with ddccontrol util. But it is not good to exec 
ddccontrol in my daemon every N seconds.

Is it possible to listen socket/pipe/something else to get such event?

---
WBR, Dmitry.


